quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Decision Making[/h1]

The [b]if[/b] statement is used to execute some code if a condition is true.

[b]Syntax:[/b] [code format="cpp"][b]if [/b](condition) {
   //statements
}[/code]
The [b]condition [/b]specifies which expression is to be evaluated. If the condition is true, the statements in the curly brackets are executed. 
[note]If the condition is [b]false[/b], the statements are simply ignored, and the program continues to run after the if statements body.[/note]

