quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The if Statement[/h1]

Use [b]relational operators[/b] to evaluate conditions.

[b]For example:[/b] [code format="cpp" codeId="191"][b]if (7 > 4)[/b] {
  cout <<  "Yes"; 
}

// Outputs "Yes"[/code]
The [b]if[/b] statement evaluates the condition (7>4), finds it to be [b]true[/b], and then executes the [b]cout [/b]statement.
If we change the greater operator to a less than operator ([b]7<4[/b]), the statement will not be executed and nothing will be printed out. 
[note]A condition specified in an if statement does not require a semicolon.[/note]

[h1]Relational Operators [/h1]

Additional relational operators: [img id="2455" width="100%"]
[b]Example:[/b] [code format="cpp" codeId="192"]if ([b]10 == 10[/b]) {
  cout <<  "Yes";
}

// Outputs "Yes"[/code]

