quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Relational Operators[/h1]

The[b] not equal to[/b] operator evaluates the operands, determines whether or not they are equal. If the operands are not equal, the condition is evaluated to [b]true[/b].
[b]For example:[/b] [code format="cpp" codeId="193"]if (10 != 10) {
  cout <<  "Yes";
}[/code]
[note]The above condition evaluates to [b]false [/b]and the block of code is not executed.[/note]

